I need to calculate the Return on Assets (ROA) for this company.

ROA is calculated as: Net Profit / Average Total Assets

Step 1: Get the Net Profit from the income statement.
Net Profit = -$1,401,436.89

Step 2: Calculate the Average Total Assets.
Initial Total Assets (2023-12-31) = $13,000,000.00
Ending Total Assets (2024-01-30) = $14,089,860.66
Average Total Assets = ($13,000,000.00 + $14,089,860.66) / 2 = $13,544,930.33

Step 3: Calculate ROA.
ROA = Net Profit / Average Total Assets
ROA = -$1,401,436.89 / $13,544,930.33
ROA = -0.1034 or -10.34%

Therefore, the Return on Assets (ROA) is -10.34%.
